document_data.Abilities:
He could ride a very fast ghostly [[horse]], which was possibly the ''[[phantom steed]]'' spell.{{cite book/Elminster Ascending/The Temptation of Elminster|603-605|7}} He employed at least one shielding spell. Another spell of his allowed him to conceal his facial features.

He suffered extensive bodily trauma in [[Galadorna]] during {{yearlink|764}}, which led to the loss of a leg and its replacement with a metal [[prosthetic]], as well as chronic pain issues. The elf could employ spells without properly mastering them, including one spell he employed to keep himself alive after suffering tremendous internal damage. However, that spell would be ruined if he attempted to restore himself to wholeness. Another spell of his made his horse stay still.

One of his spells created a field of nigh-impenetrable darkness over an area, another one burst to attack more than one target, and one caused flesh to melt, but could be delivered through a [[dagger]].{{cite book/Elminster Ascending/The Temptation of Elminster|684-686|15}}

He had a spell that multiplied a blade into three seeking missiles, almost certainly ''[[threesteel]]''. Another of his spells cloaked him in a defensive sphere, while still allowing him to attack out of a pinhole in the barrier. He could also cast a flight spell, almost certainly ''[[fly]]'', and also ''[[magic missile]]'', ''[[clairaudience]]'', and a guidance spell that allowed him to find buildings, likely similar to ''[[locate object]]''.{{cite book/Elminster Ascending/The Temptation of Elminster|696-699|17}}
